India’s Foreign Reserves Fall $4 Billion to $312.7 Billion

-- B y   T u s h a r   D h a r a
-- 
2011-09-30T11:31:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/india-s-foreign-reserves-fall-4-billion-to-312-7-billion.html
India ’s foreign-exchange reserves
fell $4 billion to $312.7 billion in the week ended Sept. 23,
the Mumbai-based Reserve Bank of India said in an e-mailed
statement today.  Foreign-currency assets declined $3.97 billion to $276.9
billion, while the nation’s gold reserves were stable at $28.3
billion, the central bank said.  India’s special drawing rights with the International
Monetary Fund decreased $52 million to $4.5 billion while its
reserves with the IMF contracted $35 million to $2.96 billion.
Total reserves climbed by $21.1 billion in the past year, the
bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
